pollution /pəˈluːʃən/

1. N-UNCOUNT Pollution is the process of polluting water, air, or land, especially with poisonous chemicals. 污染 

例： The fine was for the company's pollution of the air near its plants. 公司被罚款是因为它的工厂污染了周围的空气。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Pollution is poisonous or dirty substances that are polluting the water, air, or land somewhere. 污染物 

例： The level of pollution in the river was falling. 该河流受污染的程度其时正在降低。

</div>

